  "description": [
    "Southern Christian Advocate ESTABLISHED IN 1837 200 PER YEAR IN ADVANCE VOLUME 91 COLUMBIA S C THURSDAY SEPTEMBER 15 1927 NUMBER 37 A YOUNG KINGS FOLLY Make thou the grieroua service of thy father and the heavy yoke which he put upon us lighter and we will serve thee I Kings 124 And the king answered the people roughly I Kings 1213 So Israel departed to tlbeir tents I Kings 1216 Read I Kings 12 Popular Discontent Solomons reign had been a golden era in the history of Israel Wonderful pro gress in material things had been made There is striking parallel in what he had done in the development of public works roads and buildings to what has been going on in the United States during the past decade or more The people were groaning under the burden of taxation They resented the enforced labor and other grievous burdens necessarily placed upon them in the development of Sol omons program of progress The people do not always want to pay the price of progressive improvements Free people are never willing to pay for such with injustice There was popular discontent When Solomon died and his young son Rehoboam came"
